WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.240
Hi, I'm Hemal Hussain.

00:00:08.240 --> 00:00:16.200
I have spent my entire career building developer tools for machine learning and data science.

00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:21.459
I have worked at companies like DataRobot, Airbnb, and GitHub.

00:00:21.459 --> 00:00:28.280
And through all of that experience, I've observed that the most impactful tools are ones that

00:00:28.280 --> 00:00:33.119
help you share knowledge and collaborate with your colleagues.

00:00:33.119 --> 00:00:41.220
Specifically, tools that allow you to publish, share, and render technical reports and knowledge

00:00:41.220 --> 00:00:47.259
in a way that's easily discoverable, that other people can reference, is something that

00:00:47.259 --> 00:00:53.900
I have found, personally, through my experience, to be the highest impact type of tools that

00:00:53.900 --> 00:00:55.259
you can learn.

00:00:55.259 --> 00:01:01.799
And that's why I'm really excited to teach this course on Enhancing Communication & Collaboration

00:01:01.799 --> 00:01:04.480
with Jupyter Notebooks and Quarto.

00:01:04.480 --> 00:01:11.980
So as you may know, Jupyter Notebooks is a great medium in which to write technical information.

00:01:11.980 --> 00:01:18.800
You can intersperse code and prose in a natural way without having to copy and paste code

00:01:18.800 --> 00:01:21.480
from another context.

00:01:22.040 --> 00:01:29.239
You can have inline charts and interactive widgets and all kinds of things that really

00:01:29.239 --> 00:01:32.720
enhance the presentation of technical material.

00:01:32.720 --> 00:01:40.139
However, how do you go from this rich environment of a notebook to publishable content, something

00:01:40.139 --> 00:01:46.779
like a website or a blog post, or even an internal knowledge management system where

00:01:46.860 --> 00:01:52.260
If you're working on a team of data scientists, you can collaborate and look at each other's

00:01:52.260 --> 00:01:55.620
work and search each other's work.

00:01:55.620 --> 00:02:01.860
And this is something that Quarto really excels at.

00:02:01.860 --> 00:02:05.540
And this is what I want to teach in this course.

00:02:05.540 --> 00:02:12.339
So in this course, I'm going to show you how you can author documents in both Jupyter Notebooks

00:02:12.339 --> 00:02:15.580
but also in plain text markdown files.

00:02:16.419 --> 00:02:24.860
I'll also show you how you can use VS Code and the Quarto VS Code extension to aid you

00:02:24.860 --> 00:02:30.419
in creating Quarto projects and editing files.

00:02:30.419 --> 00:02:33.979
I'm going to show you how you can leverage Quarto to create different types of publications

00:02:33.979 --> 00:02:41.300
such as personal blogs, knowledge management, platforms for teams, notes, books, websites,

00:02:41.300 --> 00:02:44.100
and even presentation slides.

00:02:44.100 --> 00:02:49.259
These are all formats that I have produced myself with Quarto.

00:02:49.259 --> 00:02:55.059
I'm going to also show you how you can extend Quarto with notebook filters and extensions.

00:02:55.059 --> 00:02:59.380
I'm also going to show you how you can host websites and publications on platforms like

00:02:59.380 --> 00:03:02.740
GitHub Pages, Quarto Pub, and Netlify.

00:03:02.740 --> 00:03:07.660
I'm also going to show you how you can test your notebooks and test your documentation

00:03:07.660 --> 00:03:12.699
so that you can be sure that the code is valid and correct and is not stale.

00:03:12.699 --> 00:03:18.740
And as a bonus, I'm going to also teach how you can even create and document Python packages

00:03:18.740 --> 00:03:22.139
with a tool called NBDev and Quarto.

00:03:22.139 --> 00:03:29.619
I am a core developer on NBDev and NBDev is built on Quarto and is one of the sources

00:03:29.619 --> 00:03:36.460
of my knowledge of Quarto and one of the reasons why I am excited about it.

00:03:36.460 --> 00:03:39.139
I hope that you'll join me in this course.

00:03:39.139 --> 00:03:47.899
I think it has a lot of value for both personal growth in terms of helping you write blog

00:03:47.899 --> 00:03:54.300
posts and share information, but also is a great tool to help you up-level your teams.

00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:54.800
Thank you.

